=======%%% FINANCIAL DASHBOARD README FILE %%%=======

%%% PROJECT DESCRIPTION %%%
The Financial Dashboard is a web-based application developed using Spring Boot, providing a user-friendly interface to manage and monitor financial operations. The application includes features for tracking pending payments, supply chain management, and revenue visualization, making it ideal for small and medium-sized businesses.
The Project is running on Java17 so make sure to download jdk17 before running it.

%%% HOW TO RUN %%%
1. Clone the Repository:

    git clone <repository_url>
    cd financial-dashboard
------------------------------------
2. Set Up the Database:

    Create a MySQL database (e.g., financial_dashboard).

    Update application.properties with your database credentials:

        spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/financial_dashboard
        spring.datasource.username=<your_username>
        spring.datasource.password=<your_password>
------------------------------------
3. Install Dependencies:

    mvn install
------------------------------------
4. Run the Application:

    mvn spring-boot:run

==== OR ===
Just run this file:- "src/main/java/com/findas/Application.java"